				<li id="16776209" class="cmnt-root" data="10" data-d="1663643372000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579066/Short-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">19 Sep 2022 23:09</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16776209" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Despite its short length (you know, being a Short Sword), it has a fantastic moveset. At base it comes with Kick as it&apos;s skill, but put Square Off on this can it can actually put in some really good work. The required attributes to use it are also quite low, meaning that even for someone with a pure faith or pure intelligence build should have no problem implementing this into their arsenal. <br/><br/>The double thrust attacks for the heavies are so good that I basically use this as a heavy rapier, and it works incredibly well. The stance damage on fully charged heavies is surpisingly powerful. <br/><br/>All-in-all, highly recommend this weapon. 8/10, tad short, but it&apos;s not about the size, it&apos;s how you use it. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16776209" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16776209" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section cla