				<li id="16615863" class="cmnt-root" data="4" data-d="1649821904000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=122046" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">Lenox</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579066/Short-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">12 Apr 2022 23:51</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16615863" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">In Black Knife Catacombs, skeletons do not die and stand back up even if you hit them after &quot;killing them&quot; while on the ground.  I wouldn&apos;t be surprised if this becomes more prevalent later in the game.<br/><br/>For those situations, holy damage is useful.  On my Astrologer, I used the short sword (Astrologer starting weapon) with the Ash of War: Sacred Blade and the Sacred Affinity.<br/><br/>Being an Astrologer, I have plenty of FP to cast the Sacred Blade ranged skill for the entire catacombs.  And since &quot;the armament retains its holy essence for a while,&quot; I can usually kill one more skeleton with the infused short sword outright.  These kills work without needing to even down them first.<br/><br/>It&apos;s the first time I use my short sword on my Astrologer since low levels.  My main sword is Lazuli Glintstone Sword, which doesn&apos;t accept Ash of War applications.<br/><br/>As an Astrologer, you too might find yourself in this situation where you need to use a melee armament and have a limited selection to choose from if you didn&apos;t increase str / dex / arc / fai.  In those situations, your starting short sword might come in handy again.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16615863" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16615863" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>8</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16615863"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16615863" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="//fextralife.com/forums/download/file.php?avatar=164188_1669934157.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16615863"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
